let _markdown = "\n\nOpen Plugin is a standard for packaging agent extensions — skills, agents, rules, hooks, MCP servers, and LSP servers — into distributable plugins that any conformant tool can install and run.\n\nWhy plugins? [#why-plugins]\n\nAI coding agents are extensible through skills, hooks, and tool servers. But each of these is configured separately, with no standard way to package, share, or version them together.\n\nOpen Plugin solves this by defining a simple directory format that bundles related extensions into a single installable unit:\n\n```\nmy-plugin/\n├── .plugin/plugin.json    # Manifest\n├── skills/                # Agent capabilities\n├── agents/                # Sub-agents\n├── hooks/                 # Event automation\n├── rules/                 # Coding standards\n├── .mcp.json              # Tool servers\n└── .lsp.json              # Code intelligence\n```\n\nGet started [#get-started]\n\n<Cards>\n  <Card title=\"What Are Plugins?\" href=\"/docs/what-are-plugins\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Getting Started\" href=\"/docs/getting-started\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Integrate Plugins\" href=\"/docs/integrate-plugins\" />\n\n  <Card title=\"Specification\" href=\"/docs/specification\" />\n</Cards>\n";
